    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "5. Drum brake Inspection"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "696_3.0_jpn_11035921_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Check for oil leakage from wheel cylinder (A). Inspect the lining (B) for cracks, splits, peeling, or abnormal wear."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "6. Lining thickness Inspection"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "696_3.0_jpn_11035922_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Inspect the lining thickness (A). Lining thickness Std. 4.5mm Limit value: 1 1.0mm If it is below the limit value, replace the shoes as a set."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "7. Internal diameter of brake drum Check"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "696_3.0_jpn_11035923_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Measure the inside diameter of the brake drum. Inner diameter of drum Reference value 180.0mm Limit value: 1 181.0mm If the limit value is exceeded, replace the brake drum. Inspect the inner surface of the brake drum for scratches or abnormal wear."
    },
    {
